00:24:35,710 --> 00:24:38,380
my husband like that, too?

266
00:24:41,120 --> 00:24:44,040
Because you have so much to protect?

267
00:24:49,780 --> 00:24:52,490
You think you could just say anything?

268
00:24:53,510 --> 00:24:59,520
I think I've given you many opportunities in the past.

269
00:25:00,680 --> 00:25:04,170
Instead, you came this far by using me.

270
00:25:04,170 --> 00:25:08,790
You still have a long way to go. Well, so...

271
00:25:09,910 --> 00:25:13,100
is Yun Jin as good as me?

272
00:25:13,100 --> 00:25:14,630
What?

273
00:25:15,350 --> 00:25:18,990
You used me as Yun Jin's running mate.

274
00:25:18,990 --> 00:25:25,160
I wonder how you must've felt when I overtook her.

275
00:25:29,660 --> 00:25:32,340
Yun Jin probably doesn't know...

276
00:25:33,870 --> 00:25:37,450
how much love you have for her.

277
00:25:55,220 --> 00:26:00,510
 You'll put the Chairman in a difficult spot this way, not me.

278
00:26:02,050 --> 00:26:09,300
 10 months ago

279
00:26:09,300 --> 00:26:13,200
 Your father insisted on this after learning Seo Jae Won was on meds.

280
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:14,760
 Did you know?

281
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:23,370
What's this about?

282
00:26:26,070 --> 00:26:27,940
I said what is it?

283
00:26:27,940 --> 00:26:30,580
How could you do this to me?

284
00:26:31,250 --> 00:26:34,870
What have you been doing all this time, anyway?

285
00:26:34,870 --> 00:26:37,150
What have I done, you say?

286
00:26:37,150 --> 00:26:39,900
Who said you could behave like this?

287
00:26:42,090 --> 00:26:45,960
Don't you know how I've been living for the past seven years?

288
00:26:45,960 --> 00:26:50,620
Don't you know how I've been enduring a hellish time?

289
00:26:50,620 --> 00:26:52,530
But it was all...

290
00:26:53,330 --> 00:26:56,820
your doing, not Seo Jae Won's?

291
00:26:57,620 --> 00:27:01,720
How could you be so cruel to me? How?

292
00:27:04,980 --> 00:27:06,690
He's always been that way.

293
00:27:06,690 --> 00:27:10,850
All I did was answer the questions.

294
00:27:10,850 --> 00:27:13,390
No matter what I said,

295
00:27:13,390 --> 00:27:16,140
it would've happened, anyway.

296
00:27:23,310 --> 00:27:27,160
Are you... serious right now?

297
00:27:27,160 --> 00:27:31,190
It would've been fine if you had never dated him.

298
00:27:31,190 --> 00:27:36,120
Why did you have to choose someone like him?

299
00:27:40,420 --> 00:27:42,740
Am I really...

300
00:27:44,590 --> 00:27:47,130
your daughter?

301
00:27:47,770 --> 00:27:51,030
Do you even think of me as your daughter?

302
00:27:53,100 --> 00:27:55,870
Because of what you did...

303
00:27:55,870 --> 00:28:00,100
- Because of that, I— 
 - Just be glad it ended up this way.

304
00:28:00,100 --> 00:28:05,640
Your life would've been over if you'd had that scumbag's baby.

305
00:28:10,140 --> 00:28:12,280
You knew.

306
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:15,710
You knew?

307
00:28:18,100 --> 00:28:20,580
You knew about it?

308
00:28:24,750 --> 00:28:27,740
Of all the people,

309
00:28:27,740 --> 00:28:30,730
you can't be doing this to me.

310
00:28:30,730 --> 00:28:34,300
You can't be doing this to me!

311
00:28:34,300 --> 00:28:36,390
You're supposed to be my father.

312
00:28:36,390 --> 00:28:39,440
You're supposed to be my father!

313
00:28:41,070 --> 00:28:44,430
How could you do this to me?

314
00:28:44,430 --> 00:28:46,790
You didn't just...

315
00:28:47,390 --> 00:28:50,290
kill my baby.

316
00:28:51,460 --> 00:28:54,050
You killed me, too.

317
00:28:55,760 --> 00:28:57,980
How could you do this to me?

318
00:28:57,980 --> 00:29:00,950
How could you do this to me?

319
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:18,480
 Team Leader Yun Te Oh

320
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:50,580
 Nam Tae Ju. A police officer took a bribe.

321
00:30:50,580 --> 00:30:52,390
 A body of a man in his 30s found... no CCTVs in the area...

322
00:30:52,390 --> 00:30:55,160
 Investigation of a murder at Myeongyang Industrial Complex faced difficulty

323
00:31:50,950 --> 00:31:53,250
Long time no see, CEO Seo.

324
00:31:56,640 --> 00:31:59,170
You tried hard,

325
00:31:59,170 --> 00:32:02,860
but it's not good enough. None of that is a secret.

326
00:32:02,860 --> 00:32:05,990
There are way more interesting things than those.

327
00:32:05,990 --> 00:32:08,280
Let's talk about that later.

328
00:32:08,280 --> 00:32:11,370
It won't be fun to reveal everything now.

329
00:32:12,990 --> 00:32:15,850
You knew I'd come, didn't you?

330
00:32:23,740 --> 00:32:27,710
The audio file you're looking for desperately...

331
00:32:29,110 --> 00:32:31,070
isn't here.

332
00:32:35,040 --> 00:32:36,980
Although you don't seem interested in finding it.

333
00:32:36,980 --> 00:32:39,610
You changed a lot while you were hospitalized.

334
00:32:39,610 --> 00:32:42,850
Hand me the evidence you have.

335
00:32:42,850 --> 00:32:48,590
I'm sure you kept evidence while cleaning up after

336
00:32:48,590 --> 00:32:51,360
Kwon Yeong Ik and Kwon Yun Jin.

337
00:32:53,820 --> 00:32:55,880
Seriously.

338
00:32:56,420 --> 00:32:58,000
Wow.

339
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:00,270
What if I didn't?

340
00:33:00,270 --> 00:33:02,930
Even if I did, why would I?

341
00:33:02,930 --> 00:33:06,570
Because I have more money than Kwon Yun Jin.

342
00:33:06,570 --> 00:33:09,750
I'll pay you as much as you want.

343
00:33:11,950 --> 00:33:14,720
You knew I'd come,

344
00:33:15,750 --> 00:33:18,760
but you don't know the reason.

345
00:33:20,050 --> 00:33:23,020
You're disposable, too, after all.

346
00:33:23,020 --> 00:33:25,290
You'll be thrown out as well.

347
00:33:27,130 --> 00:33:29,320
Come to me then.

348
00:33:33,470 --> 00:33:36,790
You're the only one who cares for me.

349
00:33:38,470 --> 00:33:40,900
You're making me feel weak.

350
00:33:55,040 --> 00:33:56,730
Seo Jae Won.

351
00:34:05,100 --> 00:34:14,980

352
00:34:23,380 --> 00:34:26,200
Stop, stop...

353
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:29,610
Go check on CEO Seo. Go.

354
00:34:36,690 --> 00:34:38,750
Are you okay, Ms. Seo?

355
00:34:40,230 --> 00:34:41,920
I'm okay.

356
00:34:55,540 --> 00:34:57,740
He came in through this door.

357
00:34:57,740 --> 00:34:59,520
I'll call the security company.

358
00:34:59,520 --> 00:35:02,210
Let's change the passcode first.

359
00:35:02,210 --> 00:35:05,070
No, pack your things first.

360
00:35:05,070 --> 00:35:09,320
I think we should go to my place or somewhere else.

361
00:35:09,320 --> 00:35:11,070
I'm not going.

362
00:35:11,970 --> 00:35:15,000
- I'll stay here.
 - This happened for the second time.

363
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:18,000
Nam Tae Ju came inside the house. How can you say that?

364
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:21,360
That's exactly what they want.

365
00:35:21,360 --> 00:35:24,940
They're waiting for me to react and be afraid.

366
00:35:41,720 --> 00:35:45,170
Are you making Ah Rin's favorite fried rice?

367
00:35:48,470 --> 00:35:50,630
It must be nighttime in the US.

368
00:35:50,630 --> 00:35:52,990
Should we do a video chat?

369
00:35:54,990 --> 00:35:59,050
Something serious happened last night. Don't you want to be comforted?

370
00:35:59,050 --> 00:36:01,560
Will you keep swallowing it like this?

371
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:04,280
How is it different from the past, then?

372
00:36:11,450 --> 00:36:13,230
Are you okay?

373
00:36:13,230 --> 00:36:14,690
Yes.

374
00:36:15,850 --> 00:36:18,070
Yes, I'm okay.

375
00:36:30,870 --> 00:36:32,890
It's really tasty.

376
00:36:32,890 --> 00:36:34,640
I'm glad I didn't make it.

377
00:36:34,640 --> 00:36:36,670
Let's eat quickly and leave.

378
00:36:36,670 --> 00:36:38,990
We're busy today.

379
00:36:56,730 --> 00:36:59,230
Thank you for your courage  to do this.

380
00:36:59,230 --> 00:37:01,530
I'm sure it'll be very helpful.

381
00:37:01,530 --> 00:37:03,130
I'm not sure.

382
00:37:03,130 --> 00:37:04,950
This probably won't be enough.

383
00:37:04,950 --> 00:37:06,840
Even if we prove the Minister's crime,

384
00:37:06,840 --> 00:37:10,000
he'll likely pay a fine or be put on probation.

385
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:12,900
It's okay. The National Assembly's inspection is coming up soon.

386
00:37:12,900 --> 00:37:17,570
Being investigated itself would affect him enough.

387
00:37:17,570 --> 00:37:20,220
Please thank Jae Won for me.

388
00:37:20,220 --> 00:37:22,630
He was able to get surgery, thanks to her.

389
00:37:22,630 --> 00:37:24,200
Okay.

390
00:37:25,190 --> 00:37:27,830
What do you plan to do now?

391
00:37:29,020 --> 00:37:33,000
It'd be suspicious if I quit right away.

392
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:36,010
I'll quit when the time comes.

393
00:37:36,010 --> 00:37:38,170
Okay, then.

394
00:37:38,170 --> 00:37:42,370
Call me anytime if something comes up.

395
00:37:44,550 --> 00:37:46,120
Okay.

396
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:50,830
A valuable guest

397
00:37:50,830 --> 00:37:54,670
brought a precious present.

398
00:37:54,670 --> 00:37:56,980
I'm flattered.

399
00:37:57,930 --> 00:38:03,190
I wasn't sure what to bring since this is my first time visiting you.

400
00:38:03,190 --> 00:38:06,110
I was thinking of gifting you something expensive,

401
00:38:06,110 --> 00:38:09,510
but I thought you might find it troublesome.

402
00:38:09,510 --> 00:38:13,470
It feels like you, whom I have never met before, seem to

403
00:38:13,470 --> 00:38:18,700
read my mind better than the ones I've known for decades.

404
00:38:18,700 --> 00:38:22,810
I thought it would suit you perfectly.

405
00:38:23,500 --> 00:38:26,550
It's very pretty.

406
00:38:26,550 --> 00:38:28,260
It's

407
00:38:28,260 --> 00:38:32,900
fun to look at the curves of the leaves of this orchid.

408
00:38:32,900 --> 00:38:35,600
You certainly are knowledgeable.

409
00:38:36,210 --> 00:38:40,450
Orchids are often compared to a hermit who lives

410
00:38:40,450 --> 00:38:44,780
gracefully far away from the secular world.

411
00:38:47,130 --> 00:38:49,700
Do you think it'd be possible?

412
00:38:49,700 --> 00:38:55,660
It doesn't matter to me since I'm an old man who likes to sit here

413
00:38:55,660 --> 00:38:58,130
and enjoy the scenery.

414
00:39:01,180 --> 00:39:05,330
You don't have to get splashed with muddy water.

415
00:39:52,390 --> 00:39:54,570
I should get going now.

416
00:39:59,800 --> 00:40:02,040
See you tomorrow, Seung Gyu.

417
00:40:21,900 --> 00:40:25,090
We set aside one big obstacle.

418
00:40:25,090 --> 00:40:28,080
He could change his mind anytime.

419
00:40:28,080 --> 00:40:30,130
We need to be careful.

420
00:40:34,890 --> 00:40:36,810
Hey, Seong Hui.

421
00:40:36,810 --> 00:40:39,620
 Seung Gyu woke up, Ms. Seo.

422
00:40:39,620 --> 00:40:41,640
Yes.

423
00:40:41,640 --> 00:40:43,520
Okay, got it.

424
00:40:45,070 --> 00:40:46,380
Seung Gyu woke up.

425
00:40:46,380 --> 00:40:48,560
- Let's go.
 - Okay.

426
00:40:51,600 --> 00:40:53,790
Please check the vital signs.

427
00:40:55,150 --> 00:40:58,040
Thankfully, there are no serious problems.

428
00:40:58,040 --> 00:41:00,480
But they still need to keep an eye on him.

429
00:41:01,400 --> 00:41:05,160
Seong Hui, let's step out for a second.

430
00:41:30,570 --> 00:41:32,450
I'm sorry.

431
00:41:38,610 --> 00:41:41,680
You must've gone through a lot.

432
00:41:41,680 --> 00:41:44,770
I was so angry,

433
00:41:44,770 --> 00:41:47,330
and I couldn't believe it at first.

434
00:41:48,140 --> 00:41:51,680
I was thinking of leaving him whether he died or not.

435
00:41:54,030 --> 00:41:57,330
But I thought I should listen to his side of the story

436
00:41:59,880 --> 00:42:03,210
and wait until he wakes up, at least.

437
00:42:20,130 --> 00:42:22,000
What are you going to do?

438
00:42:25,640 --> 00:42:29,000
- CEO Kwon.
 - I'm thinking right now.

439
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:32,910
Thinking won't fix this issue.

440
00:42:32,910 --> 00:42:37,510
There's no need for us to make a move now.

441
00:42:37,510 --> 00:42:40,110
We still have time.

442
00:42:40,110 --> 00:42:43,640
She won't use Baek Seung Gyu immediately.

443
00:42:43,640 --> 00:42:45,150
You're so sure.

444
00:42:45,150 --> 00:42:47,510
Jae Won would be like that.

445
00:42:51,870 --> 00:42:53,960
What kind of deal...

446
00:42:55,230 --> 00:42:58,310
did Jae Won suggest?

447
00:42:58,310 --> 00:42:59,870
Deal?

448
00:43:00,620 --> 00:43:03,320
Did you think I wouldn't know, by chance?

449
00:43:03,320 --> 00:43:07,670
There's no way she just let you go.

450
00:43:11,770 --> 00:43:16,510
She said she'd pay me more than you.

451
00:43:16,510 --> 00:43:21,680
She said, "There's no way you didn't save evidence while cleaning up."

452
00:43:25,750 --> 00:43:27,820
It sounds like...

453
00:43:28,620 --> 00:43:30,730
you have evidence.

454
00:43:30,730 --> 00:43:33,480
How disappointing.

455
00:43:33,480 --> 00:43:35,950
How could that be?

456
00:43:35,950 --> 00:43:38,510
Just look who I'm with right now.

457
00:44:24,400 --> 00:44:26,680
Keep looking.

458
00:44:31,570 --> 00:44:32,740
What is it?

459
00:44:32,740 --> 00:44:35,980
Minister, you need to see the news.

460
00:44:37,490 --> 00:44:39,050
 Here's breaking news.

461
00:44:39,050 --> 00:44:41,790
 Yein Scholarship Foundation, an art scholarship foundation, is being

462
00:44:41,790 --> 00:44:44,810
 accused of accepting hundreds of millions won in bribes,

463
00:44:44,810 --> 00:44:46,690
 embezzling donation money and corrupt recruitment.

464
00:44:46,690 --> 00:44:50,390
 The Prosecutors' Office initiated a search and seizure procedure.

465
00:44:50,390 --> 00:44:54,140
 Yein Scholarship Foundation was founded by Minister Kwon Yeong Ik...

466
00:44:54,140 --> 00:44:55,460
 Yes, Minister.

467
00:44:55,460 --> 00:44:57,580
I need to schedule a meeting with Assemblyman Park immediately.

468
00:44:57,580 --> 00:44:59,610
I have a lot to discuss with him.

469
00:44:59,610 --> 00:45:05,210
Well, you won't be able to see him since his schedule is full right now.

470
00:45:05,210 --> 00:45:07,210
What are you talking about?

471
00:45:07,210 --> 00:45:09,240
 I'll hang up now.

472
00:45:35,590 --> 00:45:39,850
 For accepting hundreds of millions won in bribes, embezzling donation money

473
00:45:39,850 --> 00:45:42,470
 and corrupt recruitment.

474
00:45:46,420 --> 00:45:47,660
 Request for leave of absence

475
00:45:50,190 --> 00:45:52,400
- What's this?
 - I want to take a break

476
00:45:52,400 --> 00:45:54,750
for about six months.

477
00:45:58,350 --> 00:46:02,840
Do you think I'll accept this?

478
00:46:02,840 --> 00:46:06,030
I've never taken a break for four years.

479
00:46:06,030 --> 00:46:08,310
But I think I can take a break now

480
00:46:08,310 --> 00:46:13,370
that we have a new CEO who suits the position.

481
00:46:15,100 --> 00:46:16,960
Do you find this funny?

482
00:46:17,860 --> 00:46:20,200
I'm being serious.

483
00:46:20,200 --> 00:46:22,030
Is something going on, by the way?

484
00:46:22,030 --> 00:46:23,930
You don't look so happy.

485
00:46:27,560 --> 00:46:32,130
You guys made a mistake.

486
00:46:32,130 --> 00:46:35,200
Derêve will end up getting hurt, too.

487
00:46:35,200 --> 00:46:40,200
Maybe you're the only one who's getting hurt.

488
00:46:43,850 --> 00:46:45,660
Baek Seung Gyu...

489
00:46:48,830 --> 00:46:51,020
Where did you hide him?

490
00:47:05,670 --> 00:47:07,560
 You have your family, your company,

491
00:47:07,560 --> 00:47:11,650
 and your perfect image. You have so much to lose,

492
00:47:12,570 --> 00:47:13,920
 but I don't.

493
00:47:13,920 --> 00:47:17,950
 I can give up on family and art, too.

494
00:47:17,950 --> 00:47:20,120
 But can you?

495
00:47:53,070 --> 00:47:56,490
Seo Jae Won did work with Assemblyman Park.

496
00:47:59,380 --> 00:48:01,880
How about my payment...

497
00:48:06,100 --> 00:48:07,410
What's this?

498
00:48:07,410 --> 00:48:12,380
It's a scoop you'd be very interested in.

499
00:48:13,640 --> 00:48:17,840
But I get to decide when to publish.

500
00:48:17,840 --> 00:48:22,870
 Pesticide intake case at a closed factory

501
00:48:25,470 --> 00:48:27,210
 Murder weapon No.

502
00:48:27,210 --> 00:48:28,460
 Baek Seung Gyu

503
00:48:28,460 --> 00:48:30,040
 Kwon Yeong Ik

504
00:48:30,040 --> 00:48:31,420
 Nam Tae Ju

505
00:48:34,240 --> 00:48:39,770
 Heo Sun Yeong, Kwon Yun Jin – affair

506
00:48:46,550 --> 00:48:49,360
Sunbaenim, aren't you clocking out?

507
00:48:49,360 --> 00:48:52,020
I had to look over some files.

508
00:48:52,020 --> 00:48:54,100
- I see.
 - How about you?

509
00:48:54,100 --> 00:48:57,050
I'm picking up something, too.

510
00:48:57,050 --> 00:48:59,110
- Detective Lee.
 - Yes.

511
00:48:59,110 --> 00:49:04,270
What was the reason Seo Jae Won was arrested without a warrant?

512
00:49:05,100 --> 00:49:07,210
The crime scene wasn't their home

513
00:49:07,210 --> 00:49:10,900
and he was found in a factory complex far away from it.

514
00:49:10,900 --> 00:49:16,270
The circumstantial evidence was very clear, as you know.

515
00:49:16,270 --> 00:49:18,290
The divorce article and the issue at the company, too.

516
00:49:18,290 --> 00:49:20,250
Were there any other suspects besides Seo Jae Won?

517
00:49:20,250 --> 00:49:22,800
How about Kim Sang Beom or Kwon Yun Jin?

518
00:49:22,800 --> 00:49:28,070
It wasn't necessary to investigate them since they both had alibis.

519
00:49:29,800 --> 00:49:31,250
Okay, then.

520
00:49:31,250 --> 00:49:33,870
I'll leave you to it, then.

521
00:49:41,540 --> 00:49:46,410
He didn't know Kwon Yun Jin's alibi was false?

522
00:49:49,680 --> 00:49:51,780
Why can't we reach Assemblyman Park?

523
00:49:51,780 --> 00:49:52,930
What are his secretaries doing?

524
00:49:52,930 --> 00:49:55,250
We keep trying to reach him.

525
00:50:01,910 --> 00:50:04,170
What are you doing at home?

526
00:50:08,410 --> 00:50:12,980
I suppose you can't reach Assemblyman Park.

527
00:50:23,260 --> 00:50:28,300
Shouldn't you make a decision now?

528
00:50:35,110 --> 00:50:39,510
 Kwon Yeong Ik was definitely at the crime scene.

529
00:50:39,510 --> 00:50:43,530
 Because the audio file would've hurt him the most.

530
00:50:43,530 --> 00:50:45,920
 How about Kwon Yun Jin, then?

531
00:50:48,830 --> 00:50:50,040
How about Nam Tae Ju?

532
00:50:50,040 --> 00:50:52,930
He came to your house, too.

